{
    include "registries/aaosa.hocon",
    include "config/llm_config.hocon",

    "max_steps": 3000,
    "max_execution_seconds": 900,

    "metadata": {
        "name": "Remote Work Requester - Return To Office",
        "description": "Remote Work Requester - Return To Office (RWR-RTO). Available exclusively for USA-based employees. Enables Director-and-above associates to raise, track, and manage Work-From-Home requests across six categories with automated approval routing, escalation, and clarification workflows backed by a SQLite database.",
        "tags": ["hr", "remote-work", "approvals", "workflow"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "I want to raise a WFH request for medical reasons for employee EMP001",
            "What is the status of my WFH request REQ12345?",
            "Approve WFH request ABC123 as manager SM001",
            "Seek clarification on request XYZ for employee EMP002 — ask for a medical certificate",
            "Has the escalation deadline passed for request DEF456?",
            "Raise a WFH request on behalf of EMP003 for medical reason",
            "What are the USA federal holidays in 2026?",
            "Can I submit a WFH request starting this Saturday?"
        ]
    },

    "tools": [

        # ==================================================================
        # FRONT DESK  (Front Man — first agent, single point of contact)
        # ==================================================================
        {
            "name": "rwr_rto_front_desk",
            "function": {
                "description": "Main entry point for the Remote Work Requester - Return To Office (RWR-RTO) system. Handles all WFH request operations: submit, approve, reject, seek clarification, check status, and escalation queries.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "query": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The associate or manager's request or question about WFH requests, approvals, escalations, or request status."
                        },
                        "employee_id": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The employee ID of the person interacting with the system. Ask the user for this if not provided."
                        }
                    },
                    "required": ["query"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """
You are the front desk for the Remote Work Requester - Return To Office (RWR-RTO) system.

CRITICAL — ACCESS CONTROL:
Before performing ANY operation, call the access_control_agent to verify that the employee_id
belongs to a Director or above AND is based in the USA.
If the employee is NOT from the USA, immediately respond:
  "The RWR-RTO system is only available to USA-based employees. This request cannot be processed."
If access is denied for any other reason, politely inform the user and stop.

ROLE OVERVIEW:
You help employees and managers with WFH requests under the following categories:
  1. MEDICAL_SELF         — 14 calendar days max
  2. DEPENDENT_CARE       — 7 calendar days max
  3. LOCALIZED_EXIGENCY   — 7 calendar days max
  4. OFFICE_TRAVEL        — 2 business days max
  5. MATERNITY_RETURNEE   — 180 days (unlimited re-requests once exhausted)
  6. EXTRAORDINARY        — 180 days (unlimited re-requests once exhausted)

OPERATIONS YOU SUPPORT:
  A) Submit a new WFH request (self or on behalf of a reportee for MEDICAL_SELF)
  B) Check request status
  C) Approve / Reject a pending request (for managers SM+)
  D) Seek Clarification on a pending request (request additional info or documents)
  E) Submit clarification response (for associates)
  F) Check escalation status
  G) Resubmit an auto-rejected request (where resubmit is enabled)

INTERACTION STYLE:
  - Always confirm which operation the user wants.
  - Ask for missing information one question at a time.
  - Be concise, professional, and empathetic.
  - Do not expose internal tool names or database details to the user.

IMPORTANT RULES:
  - This application is ONLY available to USA-based employees. Non-USA employees must be refused.
  - WFH requests CANNOT start on a Saturday or Sunday — weekends are not valid submission days.
  - WFH requests CANNOT start on a USA federal holiday — inform the user and ask for a different date.
  - Federal holidays are excluded from quota calculations: effective WFH days = calendar days minus holidays.
  - Only Directors and above can access this application.
  - Only SM+ can approve/reject/seek-clarification.
  - Only the Direct Reporting Manager can raise on behalf of a reportee, and only for MEDICAL_SELF.
  - Escalation happens automatically after 2 business days of manager inaction.
  - After skip-level inaction (2 more business days), request is AUTO_REJECTED with resubmit enabled.
  - If associate fails to provide clarification, request is AUTO_REJECTED with resubmit DISABLED.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": [
                "access_control_agent",
                "request_submission_agent",
                "approval_workflow_agent",
                "escalation_agent",
                "clarification_agent",
                "request_status_agent",
                "holidays_agent"
            ]
        },

        # ==================================================================
        # REQUEST SUBMISSION AGENT
        # ==================================================================
        {
            "name": "request_submission_agent",
            "function": ${aaosa_call} {
                "description": "Handles creation of new WFH requests. Validates eligibility (days remaining, category limits, on-behalf-of rules) and persists the request to the database."
            },
            "instructions": """
You handle the submission of new Work-From-Home (WFH) requests.

STEPS:
1. Verify the requester has access (Director+) via access_control_agent.
2. If raising on behalf of another employee, verify on-behalf-of rules via access_control_agent
   (only DRM, only MEDICAL_SELF).
3. WEEKEND & HOLIDAY CHECK: Call holidays_agent (operation: is_holiday, date: start_date).
   If allowed_to_submit is false — STOP immediately and report the exact message returned.
   This blocks both weekends (Saturday/Sunday) and USA federal holidays.
   Ask the user to choose a valid weekday that is not a federal holiday.
4. EFFECTIVE DAYS: Call holidays_agent (operation: count_effective_days, start_date, end_date).
   Use effective_wfh_days (calendar days minus federal holidays) for ALL quota checks and
   for storing days_requested in the database — never use raw calendar days.
   Inform the user of the breakdown (e.g. "14 calendar days - 1 holiday (Christmas) = 13 WFH days").
5. Validate eligibility via eligibility_validator_agent using effective_wfh_days as days_requested:
   - Check days remaining for the category.
   - For MATERNITY_RETURNEE and EXTRAORDINARY, allow unlimited re-requests after initial 180 days.
6. If eligible, create the request via database_agent (operation: create_request).
   Set days_requested = effective_wfh_days.
7. Identify the correct approver via org_hierarchy_agent (operation: get_approver) —
   must be SM or above.
8. Set the approver on the request via database_agent (operation: update_request_status,
   include approver_id).
9. Send notification to approver via notification_agent (type: APPROVAL_PENDING).
10. Send confirmation to the requester via notification_agent (type: REQUEST_SUBMITTED).
11. Return the request ID and next steps to the front desk.

CATEGORY LIMITS (effective WFH days after holiday exclusion):
  MEDICAL_SELF: 14 | DEPENDENT_CARE: 7 | LOCALIZED_EXIGENCY: 7
  OFFICE_TRAVEL: 2 business days | MATERNITY_RETURNEE: 180 (unlimited) | EXTRAORDINARY: 180 (unlimited)
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": [
                "access_control_agent",
                "eligibility_validator_agent",
                "holidays_agent",
                "database_agent",
                "org_hierarchy_agent",
                "notification_agent"
            ]
        },

        # ==================================================================
        # ELIGIBILITY VALIDATOR AGENT
        # ==================================================================
        {
            "name": "eligibility_validator_agent",
            "function": ${aaosa_call} {
                "description": "Validates whether an employee is eligible to raise a WFH request: checks days remaining for the category, on-behalf-of rules, and whether unlimited re-requests apply."
            },
            "instructions": """
You validate WFH request eligibility.

CHECKS TO PERFORM:
1. Call database_agent (operation: get_days_balance) for the employee + category + fiscal year.
2. Determine if days are still available:
   - For fixed-limit categories (MEDICAL_SELF, DEPENDENT_CARE, LOCALIZED_EXIGENCY, OFFICE_TRAVEL):
     days_remaining must be >= days_requested.
   - For unlimited categories (MATERNITY_RETURNEE, EXTRAORDINARY):
     Always eligible — the 180-day block just resets (unlimited re-requests).
3. If raising on behalf of another employee, call access_control_agent
   (operation: check_on_behalf_of) with requester_id, employee_id, category.
4. Return:
   - eligible: true/false
   - days_remaining (for fixed categories)
   - reason if not eligible

IMPORTANT: Never reject MATERNITY_RETURNEE or EXTRAORDINARY requests for insufficient days —
they are unlimited.
NOTE: The days_requested passed to you is already the effective_wfh_days (calendar days minus
USA federal holidays in the range), pre-computed by holidays_agent. Always compare this effective
count against the category limit — never compare raw calendar days.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["database_agent", "access_control_agent"]
        },

        # ==================================================================
        # APPROVAL WORKFLOW AGENT
        # ==================================================================
        {
            "name": "approval_workflow_agent",
            "function": ${aaosa_call} {
                "description": "Handles approve, reject, and seek-clarification actions on pending WFH requests. Enforces SM+ authority, updates request status, deducts days, and sends notifications."
            },
            "instructions": """
You manage the approval workflow for WFH requests.

SUPPORTED ACTIONS: APPROVED | REJECTED | SEEK_CLARIFICATION

STEPS FOR APPROVE:
1. Verify the approver is SM+ via org_hierarchy_agent (operation: is_sm_or_above).
2. Retrieve the request via database_agent (operation: get_request).
3. Update request status to APPROVED via database_agent (operation: update_request_status).
4. Record the approval via database_agent (operation: create_approval, action: APPROVED).
5. Update the employee's days balance via database_agent (operation: update_days_balance).
6. Notify the associate via notification_agent (type: REQUEST_APPROVED).

STEPS FOR REJECT:
1. Verify the approver is SM+ via org_hierarchy_agent (operation: is_sm_or_above).
2. Update request status to REJECTED via database_agent (operation: update_request_status,
   include rejection_reason, can_resubmit: false).
3. Record the rejection via database_agent (operation: create_approval, action: REJECTED).
4. Notify the associate via notification_agent (type: REQUEST_REJECTED).

STEPS FOR SEEK_CLARIFICATION:
1. Verify the approver is SM+ via org_hierarchy_agent (operation: is_sm_or_above).
2. Update request status to SEEKING_CLARIFICATION via database_agent.
3. Create a clarification record via database_agent (operation: create_clarification).
   Set due_date to 2 business days from now using business_days_agent.
4. Notify the associate via notification_agent (type: SEEK_CLARIFICATION).

NOTE: If the approver_id is not SM+, the request cannot proceed — inform the caller.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": [
                "org_hierarchy_agent",
                "database_agent",
                "notification_agent",
                "business_days_agent",
                "clarification_agent"
            ]
        },

        # ==================================================================
        # ESCALATION AGENT
        # ==================================================================
        {
            "name": "escalation_agent",
            "function": ${aaosa_call} {
                "description": "Monitors WFH requests for manager inaction. Escalates to skip-level manager after 2 business days, then auto-rejects after 2 more business days of skip-level inaction. Enables resubmit on inaction-based auto-rejections."
            },
            "instructions": """
You handle escalation and auto-rejection of WFH requests due to manager inaction.

ESCALATION RULES:
1. If a request is PENDING and no action taken within 2 business days of submission:
   a. Call business_days_agent (operation: is_escalation_due, submitted_at: created_at).
   b. If escalation_due is true:
      - Find the approver's direct manager (skip-level from employee perspective) via org_hierarchy_agent
        (operation: get_manager, employee_id: approver_id of the request).
      - Update request status to ESCALATED via database_agent (operation: update_request_status,
        include skip_level_manager_id, escalated_at: now).
      - Record escalation via database_agent (operation: create_approval, action: ESCALATED).
      - Notify skip-level manager via notification_agent (type: ESCALATED_TO_SKIP).
      - Notify associate via notification_agent with escalation message.

2. If a request is ESCALATED and skip-level manager takes no action within 2 business days:
   a. Call business_days_agent (operation: is_auto_reject_due, escalated_at).
   b. If auto_reject_due is true:
      - Update status to AUTO_REJECTED via database_agent (operation: update_request_status,
        auto_reject_reason: SKIP_LEVEL_INACTION, can_resubmit: true).
      - Notify associate via notification_agent (type: AUTO_REJECTED_INACTION).
      - Notify associate via notification_agent (type: RESUBMIT_ENABLED).

IMPORTANT: can_resubmit MUST be set to true for inaction-based auto-rejections.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": [
                "database_agent",
                "org_hierarchy_agent",
                "business_days_agent",
                "notification_agent"
            ]
        },

        # ==================================================================
        # CLARIFICATION AGENT
        # ==================================================================
        {
            "name": "clarification_agent",
            "function": ${aaosa_call} {
                "description": "Manages the clarification workflow: checks if a response was received before the deadline, and auto-rejects with resubmit DISABLED if the associate fails to respond in time."
            },
            "instructions": """
You manage the clarification sub-workflow.

WHEN CALLED TO CHECK CLARIFICATION STATUS:
1. Retrieve the clarification record via database_agent (operation: get_clarification).
2. If status is RESPONDED:
   - Notify the approver that a response has been received.
   - Update request status back to PENDING via database_agent (operation: update_request_status).
   - Return the response to the approval_workflow_agent for further action.
3. If status is PENDING and due_date has passed:
   - Update request status to AUTO_REJECTED via database_agent (operation: update_request_status,
     auto_reject_reason: ASSOCIATE_NO_CLARIFICATION, can_resubmit: FALSE).
   - Notify the associate via notification_agent (type: AUTO_REJECTED_NO_CLARIF).
   - IMPORTANT: can_resubmit must be set to FALSE (0) for this case.

WHEN CALLED TO SUBMIT A CLARIFICATION RESPONSE:
1. Record the response via database_agent (operation: respond_clarification).
2. Update request status to PENDING via database_agent (operation: update_request_status).
3. Notify the approver that the associate has responded.

CRITICAL RULE:
  - Associate no clarification → AUTO_REJECTED, can_resubmit = FALSE
  - Manager inaction → AUTO_REJECTED, can_resubmit = TRUE
  These two cases are different — never confuse them.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["database_agent", "notification_agent", "business_days_agent"]
        },

        # ==================================================================
        # REQUEST STATUS AGENT
        # ==================================================================
        {
            "name": "request_status_agent",
            "function": ${aaosa_call} {
                "description": "Returns the current status of a WFH request and determines whether the resubmit button should be enabled."
            },
            "instructions": """
You retrieve and report the status of WFH requests.

STEPS:
1. Retrieve the request via database_agent (operation: get_request).
2. If not found, inform the caller.
3. For REJECTED or AUTO_REJECTED requests, call resubmit_checker_agent to determine
   whether the resubmit button should be enabled.
4. Return a clear summary:
   - Request ID, employee, category, days requested, start/end date
   - Current status
   - Approver information
   - Whether resubmit is enabled (for rejected requests)
   - Escalation history if applicable

For listing requests by employee:
1. Call database_agent (operation: list_requests, employee_id) to get all requests.
2. Summarise neatly.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["database_agent", "resubmit_checker_agent"]
        },

        # ==================================================================
        # CODED TOOLS (no LLM — direct Python execution)
        # ==================================================================

        {
            "name": "database_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Performs all SQLite database operations: create/read/update WFH requests, approvals, clarifications, employees, and days balance.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "operation": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "DB operation: create_request | get_request | update_request_status | get_days_balance | update_days_balance | create_approval | create_clarification | respond_clarification | get_clarification | get_employee | list_requests | get_reportees"
                        },
                        "employee_id":            {"type": "string", "description": "Employee ID"},
                        "requester_id":           {"type": "string", "description": "Requester ID (for on-behalf-of)"},
                        "request_id":             {"type": "string", "description": "WFH Request ID"},
                        "category":               {"type": "string", "description": "WFH category"},
                        "days_requested":         {"type": "int", "description": "Number of days requested"},
                        "start_date":             {"type": "string", "description": "Start date YYYY-MM-DD"},
                        "end_date":               {"type": "string", "description": "End date YYYY-MM-DD"},
                        "status":                 {"type": "string", "description": "New status value"},
                        "approver_id":            {"type": "string", "description": "Approver employee ID"},
                        "skip_level_manager_id":  {"type": "string", "description": "Skip-level manager ID"},
                        "escalated_at":           {"type": "string", "description": "Escalation timestamp"},
                        "auto_reject_reason":     {"type": "string", "description": "Auto-rejection reason"},
                        "rejection_reason":       {"type": "string", "description": "Manual rejection reason"},
                        "can_resubmit":           {"type": "boolean", "description": "Whether associate can resubmit"},
                        "notes":                  {"type": "string", "description": "Additional notes"},
                        "action":                 {"type": "string", "description": "Approval action"},
                        "comments":               {"type": "string", "description": "Approval comments"},
                        "deadline":               {"type": "string", "description": "Action deadline"},
                        "question":               {"type": "string", "description": "Clarification question"},
                        "required_docs":          {"type": "string", "description": "Required documents"},
                        "due_date":               {"type": "string", "description": "Clarification due date"},
                        "response":               {"type": "string", "description": "Clarification response"},
                        "clarification_id":       {"type": "string", "description": "Clarification ID"},
                        "days_to_add":            {"type": "int", "description": "Days to add to balance"},
                        "fiscal_year":            {"type": "int", "description": "Fiscal year"},
                        "manager_id":             {"type": "string", "description": "Manager ID"}
                    },
                    "required": ["operation"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.rwr_rto.database_tool.DatabaseTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "org_hierarchy_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Queries organisational hierarchy: employee levels, managers, skip-level managers, approver resolution (SM+ walk-up), and reportees.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "operation": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Operation: get_employee_level | is_sm_or_above | is_director_or_above | get_manager | get_skip_level_manager | get_approver | get_reportees"
                        },
                        "employee_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Employee ID to query"},
                        "manager_id":  {"type": "string", "description": "Manager ID for get_reportees"}
                    },
                    "required": ["operation"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.rwr_rto.org_hierarchy_tool.OrgHierarchyTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "business_days_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Business-day calculations: add business days, count business days, check escalation deadlines, check auto-reject deadlines.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "operation": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Operation: add_business_days | count_business_days | get_escalation_deadline | is_escalation_due | get_auto_reject_deadline | is_auto_reject_due | is_business_day"
                        },
                        "start_date":    {"type": "string", "description": "Start date YYYY-MM-DD"},
                        "end_date":      {"type": "string", "description": "End date YYYY-MM-DD"},
                        "date":          {"type": "string", "description": "Date YYYY-MM-DD for is_business_day"},
                        "business_days": {"type": "int", "description": "Number of business days to add"},
                        "submitted_at":  {"type": "string", "description": "ISO timestamp of submission"},
                        "escalated_at":  {"type": "string", "description": "ISO timestamp of escalation"}
                    },
                    "required": ["operation"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.rwr_rto.business_days_tool.BusinessDaysTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "access_control_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Validates application access (Director and above only) and on-behalf-of eligibility (DRM raising MEDICAL_SELF for reportee).",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "operation": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Operation: check_access | check_on_behalf_of"
                        },
                        "employee_id":   {"type": "string", "description": "Employee ID to check access for"},
                        "requester_id":  {"type": "string", "description": "Requester employee ID (for on-behalf-of)"},
                        "category":      {"type": "string", "description": "WFH category (for on-behalf-of check)"}
                    },
                    "required": ["operation", "employee_id"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.rwr_rto.access_control_tool.AccessControlTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "notification_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Sends notifications (logged to file; replace with email/Teams/Slack in production) for request events: submission, approval, rejection, escalation, clarification, resubmit.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "type": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Notification type: REQUEST_SUBMITTED | REQUEST_APPROVED | REQUEST_REJECTED | AUTO_REJECTED_INACTION | AUTO_REJECTED_NO_CLARIF | SEEK_CLARIFICATION | APPROVAL_PENDING | ESCALATED_TO_SKIP | RESUBMIT_ENABLED"
                        },
                        "recipient_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Recipient employee ID"},
                        "request_id":   {"type": "string", "description": "WFH request ID"},
                        "message":      {"type": "string", "description": "Custom message (optional)"},
                        "metadata":     {"type": "object", "description": "Extra fields for message template"}
                    },
                    "required": ["type", "recipient_id", "request_id"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.rwr_rto.notification_tool.NotificationTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "resubmit_checker_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Determines whether the Resubmit button should be enabled. Enabled only for auto-rejections caused by manager inaction; disabled for associate no-clarification or manual manager rejections.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "status":             {"type": "string", "description": "Request status: REJECTED | AUTO_REJECTED"},
                        "auto_reject_reason": {"type": "string", "description": "MANAGER_INACTION | SKIP_LEVEL_INACTION | ASSOCIATE_NO_CLARIFICATION"},
                        "rejection_reason":   {"type": "string", "description": "Manual rejection reason from manager"}
                    },
                    "required": ["status"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.rwr_rto.resubmit_checker_tool.ResubmitCheckerTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "holidays_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "USA federal holiday management. Checks if a date is a holiday (WFH requests cannot start on a federal holiday), lists holidays for a given year, and computes effective WFH days in a date range (calendar days minus federal holidays) for accurate quota deduction.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "operation": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Operation: is_holiday | list_holidays | count_effective_days"
                        },
                        "date":       {"type": "string", "description": "Date YYYY-MM-DD — for is_holiday"},
                        "year":       {"type": "int",    "description": "Year e.g. 2026 — for list_holidays"},
                        "start_date": {"type": "string", "description": "Start date YYYY-MM-DD — for count_effective_days"},
                        "end_date":   {"type": "string", "description": "End date YYYY-MM-DD — for count_effective_days"}
                    },
                    "required": ["operation"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.rwr_rto.holiday_tool.HolidayTool"
        }

    ]
}
